Global Capability Centers (GCCs) play a vital role in managing essential business functions for global organizations across various functions, such as IT, finance, human resources, R&D, etc. They help organizations boost productivity, streamline processes and stay competitive in a rapidly evolving global market. 
#DYK, India is projected to have over 2,400 GCCs by 2030! 
Watch the video to know more.
#Technology #Innovation #BusinessGrowth #Businesses

The #Budget2025 includes a range of growth-enhancing measures that will go a long way in realizing India’s vision of a ‘Viksit Bharat’ by supporting inclusive growth and development, while promoting livelihoods and employment. Bold initiatives, including huge income tax relief to the middle class with no income tax up to ₹12 lakh and indirect tax changes, will strongly boost consumption in the economy, writes Chandrajit Banerjee, Director General, CII. Read his views on #UnionBudget2025 in #CIIBlog https://bit.ly/4gv4Nna

This year’s Budget focuses on four powerful engines of growth and introduces reforms for agriculture, MSMEs, investment, and exports. In a substantial boost to the middle and salaried class, the announcement of no income tax up to Rs 12 lakh in the new tax regime greatly enhances consumption in the economy by boosting disposable incomes and encouraging savings.
